}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 97-102.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   The following five figures were all kings rather than emperors, beginning with \softline
Ottokar of Bohemia (1253-78), who was in fact killed by Rudolph in 1278.  Just as Rudolph, for \softline
all his faults, is presented as saved, while his son Albert seems clearly not to be, so is Ottokar 
